Class Document

  • entity.Document
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Bean, EventAware, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.InsertCallback, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.RemoveCallback, Retireable, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.UpdateCallback

    public class Document
implements Bean, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.InsertCallback, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.UpdateCallback, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.RemoveCallback, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.InsertCallback, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.UpdateCallback, com.guidewire.pl.system.bundle.RemoveCallback, Retireable, EventAware
    Internal representation of a physical or electronic document.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      String Author
      Name of the person who created the document.
      String AuthorDenorm
      denorm field for Name of the person who created the document.
      Integer BeanVersion
      Auto-incremented object version
      boolean CachedContentExists
      Returns the the cached status about whether the document content exists in the document content source. On the first call on the entity instance, it will call into document content source plugin to get the status and cache the result for future calls
      Date CreateTime
      Timestamp when the object was created
      User CreateUser
      User who created the object
      Boolean DMS
      Whether this document has content stored in a Document Management System.
      Date DateCreated
      Date and time the document was created.
      Date DateModified
      Date and time the document was last modified.
      String Description
      Description of the document.
      String DocUID
      The Unique Identifier (UID) for this document. The format of this UID is specific to the deployed Document Management System (DMS), and is passed to the configured IDocumentContentSource implementation.
      String DocumentIdentifier
      Short human-readable identifier for the document, often used as an extra storage location for form codes, when name and documenttype are inadequate.
      String DocumentIdentifierDenorm
      denorm field for Short human-readable identifier for the document, often used as an extra storage location for form codes, when name and documenttype are inadequate.
      ILocale DocumentLanguage
      Gets the language in which the document was created in. A null value means that it is not clear which language the document was created in. Most possibly, it is the default locale of the application.
      Key ID
      Internally managed primary key
      String Icon
      Returns the name of an icon image to represent this document. The result is based on the document's mime type.
      Boolean Inbound
      Whether the document is an inbound, outbound, or stationary (null) document
      LanguageType Language
      The language in which this document is created.
      Long LoadCommandID
      LoadCommand for load where row was created. If not null this object was loaded via the loader.
      ILocale Locale
      Gets the locale in which the document was created in. A null value means that it is not clear which language the document was created in. Most possibly, it is the default locale of the application.
      String MimeType
      The MIME type of this document; for example, application/msword for a Microsoft Word document.
      String Name
      Human-readable name of the document.
      String NameDenorm
      denorm field for Human-readable name of the document.
      Boolean Obsolete
      If true, the information in the document can no longer be relied upon to be up-to-date and relevant. This is often used instead of deletion to preserve history.
      String PendingDocUID
      The document is pending, and it's pending storage has Unique Identifier (UID). The format of this UID is specific to the IDCS implementation.
      String PublicID
      ID or primary key of the row in the external system to which this row is mapped
      String Recipient
      Name of the intended recipient of the document (if any).
      Long RetiredValue
      Whether the entity is still in use. A value of 0 means that the entity is not retired. If the entity is retired from active use, this field has a non-zero value equal to the entity's ID. Once an entity is retired, it should not be unretired.
      DocumentSection Section
      The section to which this document belongs, if any.
      DocumentSecurityType SecurityType
      Type of document used for access-restriction purposes, in conjunction with the information in security-config.xml.
      DocumentStatusType Status
      The current status of the document, if any.
      DocumentType Type
      The specific type of the document, if any.
      Date UpdateTime
      Timestamp when the object was last updated
      User UpdateUser
      User who last updated the object
